# UI Restructuring and Appointment Logic Fixes

This document outlines the approach for restructuring the application into a 5-tab layout and fixing core scheduling and appointment edge cases as requested by the user.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> Please review this plan. The UI restructuring involves moving the current Dashboard into the "Home" tab of a new persistent Bottom Navigation layout.
> Setting a 30-minute strict interval requires modifying time selection inputs across the app to use dropdowns or grid selectors instead of the native open-ended clock pickers.

## Proposed Changes

### Main Layout Structure (5 Tabs)
--------------------------------------
To provide immediate access to core module areas, we will implement a [MainLayout](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/dashboard/screens/main_layout.dart#11-17) scaffold that wraps the app after login.

#### [NEW] [lib/features/dashboard/screens/main_layout.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/dashboard/screens/main_layout.dart)
- Create a `StatefulWidget` or Riverpod-driven screen to manage a `BottomNavigationBar`.
- Define 5 tabs:
  1. Home ([DoctorDashboardScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/dashboard/screens/doctor_dashboard_screen.dart#9-263) / [ClinicDashboardScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/dashboard/screens/clinic_dashboard_screen.dart#8-253))
  2. Appointments ([AppointmentListScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart#10-17))
  3. Analytics (Placeholder screen for now)
  4. Patients (Placeholder list for now)
  5. Settings ([SettingsScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/settings/screens/settings_screen.dart#12-18))

#### [MODIFY] [lib/core/router/app_router.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/router/app_router.dart)
- Change the `/dashboard` route to render [MainLayout](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/dashboard/screens/main_layout.dart#11-17) instead of the direct dashboard screens.
- Refactor the existing `_DashboardRouter` proxy class (if present) to resolve to [MainLayout](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/dashboard/screens/main_layout.dart#11-17).


### Time Interval Standardization (30 mins)
--------------------------------------
The system will standardize time intervals. By default, time pickers will enforce 30-minute intervals (e.g., 09:00 AM, 09:30 AM).

#### [NEW] [lib/core/widgets/time_slot_picker.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/widgets/time_slot_picker.dart)
- Replace native `showTimePicker` (which allows minute-level granularity) with a custom bottom sheet or dialog grid that specifically renders intervals based on the user's duration setting (default 30 mins).

#### [MODIFY] [lib/features/auth/screens/doctor_registration/doctor_registration_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/auth/screens/doctor_registration/doctor_registration_screen.dart)
#### [MODIFY] [lib/features/auth/screens/clinic_registration/clinic_step3_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/auth/screens/clinic_registration/clinic_step3_screen.dart)
- Form fields for "Working Hours" will use the new `time_slot_picker`.
- Add a dropdown to select default "Slot Duration" (15m, 30m, 60m) saving to the `treatments` array or a dedicated `slot_duration` setting on the [doctors](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/scripts/setup_pocketbase.dart#112-131) table.


### Appointment Logic Fixes
--------------------------------------
Appointments (both Call-By and Walk-In) should only be created when the doctor has availability, avoiding double-booking and schedule clashes.

#### [MODIFY] [lib/features/appointments/screens/create_appointment_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/create_appointment_screen.dart)
- **Availability Constraint**: When users pick a date/time for "Call-By", use the [AvailableSlotsScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/scheduling/screens/available_slots_screen.dart#12-32) to force them to select an unequivocally free time slot, exactly like walk-ins or patient scheduling. Do not allow arbitrary time entry.
- **Navigation Bug**: Ensure the [_submit](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/patient_info_screen.dart#76-139) function handles the `Navigator.pop(context)` successfully up the routing stack after the `pb.collection(appointments).create` promise resolves.

#### [MODIFY] [lib/core/services/scheduling_service.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/scheduling_service.dart)
- Ensure the [validateAppointmentTime](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/scheduling_service.dart#192-230) or creation proxy runs the exact [getConcurrentAppointments](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/scheduling_service.dart#141-168) / [isSlotBooked](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/scheduling_service.dart#178-191) logic synchronously before creating the record to enforce the **No Duplicate Appointments** rule server/client side.

## Phase 9: Home Redesign & Expendable FAB
We will simplify the dashboards and convert the new appointment action into a central floating button.
### Dashboards Simplification
- [MODIFY] [clinic_dashboard_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/dashboard/screens/clinic_dashboard_screen.dart) & [doctor_dashboard_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/dashboard/screens/doctor_dashboard_screen.dart) to remove the Quick Stats (Beds, Doctors, Patients) and Quick Actions sections to achieve a minimalist Home screen.

### Expandable Floating Action Button
- [NEW] `expandable_fab.dart` in `core/widgets/`. It will animate between an `Extended` (pill-shaped) state on the Home tab, and a standard circle state on the other tabs. When clicked, it will expand upwards with an interactive slider showing mini-buttons for **Call-By** and **Walk-In**.
- [MODIFY] [main_layout.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/dashboard/screens/main_layout.dart) to integrate the `ExpandableFab`. Use `FloatingActionButtonLocation.centerFloat` (or bottom-centered docked) so it sits directly above the 5 tabs.
- [MODIFY] [app_router.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/router/app_router.dart) and [create_appointment_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/create_appointment_screen.dart) so the appointment creation route accepts an argument (`initialIsCallBy`) mapping to the direct user choice from the FAB.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
1. Login and ensure the bottom navigation bar permanently shows 5 options.
2. Go to Settings and Registration to verify time selectors only offer discrete blocks (e.g. 30min intervals). 
3. Try to book a Call-By appointment at an explicitly conflicting time to verify rejection.
4. Try to book a valid Call-By or Walk-In appointment to verify the app navigates back correctly.
